      • _getObjectIdentifier

        protected String _getObjectIdentifier(int[] intArray,
                          int offset,
                          int length)
        Deliver an object identifier string from part of an integer array.
        Parameters:
        intArray - the source array
        offset - the offset of the first integer of the identifier
        length - the number of sub-identifiers in the identifier
        Returns:
        a string of the form "n1.n2....nn", where n1 is the integer at intArray[offset], n2 is the is the integer at intArray[offset + 1] and nn is the integer at intArray[offset + n - 1]
